Task: Finalize the Corefinity Control Panel as a high-fidelity, interactive SaaS application. Every component must be data-driven and "live."
​1. The "Pulse" (Global State & Simulation):
​Create a global useEffect timer. Every 3 seconds, generate a new set of random metrics for CPU, RAM, and Latency across the app.
​Dashboard Synergy: Ensure the "Active Deployments" card on the Dashboard reflects the actual number of "Running" tasks in the Environments tab.
​2. Dashboard: The Command Center (Image 1-5):
​Interactive Charts: Use simple CSS-based bar charts or sparklines to show "Traffic 24h" and "Resource Usage."
​Smart Activity Feed: The feed must include specific timestamps (e.g., "2 mins ago") and OrangeLinks for every entity (User, Environment, Company).
​Critical Alerts: Add an "Incident Banner" at the top of the dashboard that only appears if "System Health" drops below 98% (simulated).
​3. Environments: Deep Integration (Image 10-25):
​Tab Persistence: Ensure that clicking sub-tabs (Pods, Nodes, Firewall) updates the URL or state perfectly so the user never loses their place.
​The "Running" Terminal: In the Diagnostics tab, the terminal should auto-scroll and include timestamped logs like [08:42:01] INFO: SSL Certificate is valid for 89 days.
​Resource Gauges: In the Pods tab, use a color-changing progress bar: Green (<60%), Yellow (60-80%), Red (>80%) based on the live simulated data.
​4. The Support System: Logic Polish (Image 30-36):
​Messaging: Implement "Press Enter to Send" logic for the chat.
​Internal Toggle: When "Internal Note" is active, change the placeholder text to "Write a note for staff eyes only..." and ensure the yellow background (#FFFBEB) covers the entire input container.
​Sidebar Sync: The "Company" and "Website" links in the ticket sidebar must actually navigate the user back to that specific Environment view.
​5. Global UI/UX Perfection:
​Skeleton Loaders: Add a 0.8s loading state when switching main views (Dashboard to Environments) to simulate API fetching.
​The "Orange Link" Rule (Final Audit): Every single ID (env-xxx, tkt-xxx), Every Company Name, and Every Website Name must be #FF6B00.
​Tooltips: Add hover tooltips to technical icons (e.g., "Reboot Pod," "Copy IP," "View Commit").
​Empty States: If a search returns no results, show a "No Data Found" illustration with an "Add New" button.
